The way to avoid multiple tabs is as follows: 

    Intent intent = new Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW);
    intent.setData(uri);
    intent.putExtra(Browser.EXTRA_APPLICATION_ID, getPackageName());
    startActivity(intent);

The EXTRA_APPLICATION_ID will contain an ID of your app, and the browser will recycle a tab that was opened by your application, rather than opening a new tab.  In this way, all the pages opened by your application will share the same tab, and you will not have &quot;tab inflation&quot; in the browser.

None of the solutions above involving `Browser.EXTRA_APPLICATION_ID` work. 

